<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="231" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1012.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-22">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 22, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Chinese Government has borrowed from Diederichsen &amp; Co., a
                                German firm, 3,000,000 taels, 15 years, 6½ %. Security, likin and
                                tea.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>